{"id":83879,"date":"2020-07-01T13:50:40","date_gmt":"2020-07-01T03:50:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=83879"},"modified":"2021-10-14T15:21:40","modified_gmt":"2021-10-14T05:21:40","slug":"1-july-2020-general-skilled-migration","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/1-july-2020-general-skilled-migration\/","title":{"rendered":"1 July 2020 General Skilled Migration"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2><strong>1st July 2020, new financial year starts.<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>The <strong>General Skilled Migration (GSM)<\/strong> program for the 2019\/20 financial year has now closed.<\/p>\n<p>The State &amp; Territory nomination program <strong>will remain temporarily CLOSED<\/strong> until the Commonwealth Government\u2019s allocation of state nomination places for 2020-21 takes place. This means that State &amp; Territory governments\u2019 have no ability to nominate applicants in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-nominated-190-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">visa subclass 190<\/a> &amp; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-work-regional-491-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">visa subclass 491<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Although applications for some State and Territory nomination may remain open, during this time <strong>no nominations can be made in SkillSelect <\/strong>until quotas are allocated.<\/p>\n<p>The GSM 2020\/21 program year is scheduled to re-open from early August however, changes to the composition of the Australian Migration program might be made in October under the new budget. Due to the <a href=\"https:\/\/covid19.homeaffairs.gov.au\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Coronavirus<\/a>, the date for Federal Budget 2020-2021 has been delayed by the Federal Government &#8211; it will be handed down in Parliament on 6 October. The Federal Treasurer has advised that he will provide an update on the economic and fiscal outlook on 23 July.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bdo.com.au\/en-au\/federalbudget2020\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https:\/\/www.bdo.com.au\/en-au\/federalbudget2020<\/a><\/p>\n<p>We will provide any updates as changes occur.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Stay up to date<\/strong> following us on Social Media: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/anzscosearch\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Facebook<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/anzscosearch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twitter<\/a> &amp; <a href=\"https:\/\/instagram.com\/anzscosearch_\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Instagram<\/a>.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][nectar_global_section id=&#8221;109315&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221;&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":83887,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[90,25,129],"tags":[],"class_list":{"0":"post-83879","1":"post","2":"type-post","3":"status-publish","4":"format-standard","5":"has-post-thumbnail","7":"category-occupation-list","8":"category-news","9":"category-skilled-visa"},"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/83879","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2